What is OSI Model Layers of OSI Model
The OSI Open Systems Interconnection Model is a set of rules that explains how different computer systems communicate over a network. OSI Model was developed by the International Organization for Standardization ISO. The OSI Model consists of layers and each layer has specific functions and responsibilities. This layered approach makes it easier for different devices and technologies to work together. OSI Model provides a clear structure for data trasmission and managing network issues. The OSI Model is widely used as a reference to understand how network systems function.
Layers of the OSI Model
There are layers in the OSI Model and each layer has its specific role in handling data. All the layers are mentioned below.
